[SN]TITLE[SN]
Africa this week: Five things we've learnt

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Some of the quirkier snippets from the news in Africa that we did not know last week:

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
1) Niger has an official maximum bride price of $83
Following news that Uganda has banned bride price refunds, we found out that in Niger there is an official maximum rate a groom can pay a bride's family when they get married. It is 50,000 CFA francs ($83, Â£54) but many pay much more than this.
