4) Nairobi National Park is the nearest national park to a city in the world
The park is so close to the Kenyan capital that this elephant orphanage is on the periphery of Nairobi while still being within the confines of the park.
Find out more
5) Bonobos can squeak
Researchers have found that Bonobos from Democratic Republic of Congo do not just scream, bark and pant but also make a high-pitched squeak which shows they can communicate far more than previously thought.
